SIMPLE: safeguard
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Safeguard
<hw>Safe"guard`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Safe =
<ets>guard</ets>: cf. F. <ets>sauvegarde</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who, or that which, defends or protects; defense;
protection.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy sword, the <qex>safeguard</qex> of thy brother's throne.</q>
<rj><qau>Granville.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A convoy or guard to protect a traveler or
property.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A pass; a passport; a safe-conduct.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Safeguard</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Safeguard
<hw>Safe"guard`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To guard; to protect.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Safe-keeping</ent>⟦br⟧
